  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd6\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8\u0da7 \u0da9\u0ddc.\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 366\u0d9a \u0daf\u0da9\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A fine of USD 366 million was imposed on Google from Russia",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A Russian court has fined Google 21 billion rubles (US$366 million) for failing to delete banned information about the conflict in Ukraine, according to foreign reports.",
        "Moscow's Tagansky District Court has fined the IT company a turnover-based fine for repeatedly refusing to delete information prohibited by Russian law.",
        "Roskommandoza, the national internet and media watchdog, previously ordered the company to remove \"misleading information\" from YouTube about Russia's military offensive in Ukraine."
      ],
